The robe's patterns have evolved. Initially, designs such as ''Kiritake HЕҚЕҚmon'' (paulownia, bamboo, and phoenix motifs) were used. By the [[:en:Muromachi period|Muromachi period]], the design transitioned to rectangular ''kakugata mon'' patterns incorporating mythical creatures like the phoenix and kirin.{{sfn|йҲҙжңЁ|1985}} These patterns remain in use today.

