The robe is integral to imperial rituals, including the {{ill|Enthronement of the Japanese emperor|ja|еҚідҪҚзӨјжӯЈж®ҝгҒ®е„Җ|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Enthronement of the Japanese emperor|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}}, {{ill|Shihohai|lt=Ritual of the Four Directions|ja|еӣӣж–№жӢқ|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shihohai|qq=}}, and other key [[:en:Ritual ceremonies of the Imperial Palace|Ceremonies of the Japanese Imperial Palace]] ceremonies. Exceptions include the [[:en:Niiname-no-Matsuri|Niinamesai]], where the Emperor wears a ceremonial white robe (''gosai fuku'').

